<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC plans a one-hour, prime-time special on the
New Hampshire primary Tuesday night, and CBS' weekly documentary
show ``48 Hours'' will include live updates on the results.
   CNN will offer extended prime-time coverage of the nation's
first presidential primary of 1988.
   ABC will interrupt its coverage of the Winter Olympics for
updates and broadcast a special half-hour wrap-up at midnight EST.
   NBC scheduled a 1-hour special at 10 p.m. At 8 p.m., CBS will
air ``48 Hours on the Campaign Trail,'' a videotaped show that will
include live reports from New Hampshire.
