<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Obit-Pollack     02-15 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Pollack,0150</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sculptor, Former Saturday Evening Post Editor Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRANTSVILLE, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Merrill Pollack, a sculptor, writer
and former editor of the Saturday Evening Post, has died after a
short illness at the age of 63.
   Pollack, a New York City native and a resident of Grantsville,
died Sunday at St. Joseph's Hospital in Parkersburg. His family did
not disclose the cause of death.
   In addition to working as editor of the Saturday Evening Post in
Philadelphia, he worked as an executive editor for Viking Press and
was an editor for Simon & Schuster.
   In 1977, Pollack moved to Grantsville, where he sculpted and did
wood carvings. From 1981 to 1986, he was editor of a local
newspaper, the Calhoun County Chronicle, and served on the art
faculty at West Virginia University.
   Pollack is survived by his wife, Jeanne, five children and a
brother.
</TEXT>
