<HEAD>F-15s Intercept Soviet Transport</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANCHORAGE, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Air Force F-15 Eagle jet fighters
from King Salmon intercepted a Soviet short-range transport plane
56 miles southwest of Cape Romanzof, the Air Force said Monday.
   Master Sgt. Jack Hokanson of the Alaskan Air Command said the
F-15s intercepted the Soviet IL-Crate at about 3:35 p.m. Sunday off
Alaska's southwest coast and escorted the aircraft for about an
hour.
   So far this year, the command's jets have intercepted six Soviet
planes in four separate incidents, Hokanson said.
