<DATELINE>FRANKLIN, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wind blew over a 30-foot-high wall at a
condominium complex under construction Monday, trapping 18 workers
for about five minutes, authorities said. Ten workers were injured,
three of them seriously.
   Fire Lt. James Hagerty said the crew was using long wooden poles
to manually raise the sheetrock-and-plywood wall when it collapsed.
   ``Basically what they were doing was raising the exterior wall
to the second story of the building,'' he said. ``The wind caught
hold of the framing and becauseitions they lost
their footing and everything came on top of them.''
   Three workers were ho of the icy condspitalized with back injuries.
Seven others
had minor cuts and bruises.
