<HEAD>IRA Claims Responsibility for Killing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Irish Republican Army
claimed responsibility Monday for the fatal shooting of a part-time
soldier in the Ulster Defense Regiment.
   The claim was made in a statement to news media, delivered hours
after the Royal Ulster Constabulary said gunmen followed a
23-year-old man into the carpentry shop where he worked in Kilkeel,
County Down.
